            <opener><dateline><date when="1915-06-11">June 11, 1915.</dateline></date>
                <salute>Dear <persName key="richard_aldington">Richard</persName>:</salute></opener>
            <p>This is not a letter, but merely a note to explain the enclosed, which is <persName key="guido_bruno">Brunoâ€™s</persName>
                <title key="brunosWeekly" level="j">publication</title>. It will give you the quality of the man and his work better than I can tell you. I think,
                in fact, it will be an answer to your question as to what he is like.</p>
            <p>I have just got the bill from <orgName key="houghton_mifflin">Houghton Mifflin</orgName> for our book and advertising, <measure type="currency" num="430.98">$430.98</measure>. It is
                a bit staggering, but never mind! But I am afraid the sale will never make up the cost.</p>
        </body>
